<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
In OS_CountSemGetInfo the local variable 'record' is declared as OS_common_record_t *record; but it is only used to read fields (record->name_entry and record->creator) and is never used to modify the object. Therefore it could be declared as const OS_common_record_t *record; so it should be const-qualified to satisfy MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13. Assignment from OS_OBJECT_TABLE_GET (which yields OS_common_record_t *) to a const-qualified pointer is allowed; no writes occur through 'record'.
</scenario>

